         "5": "501",
         "6": "1. Stored Procedure Name: dbo.uspCalculateAnnualSummaryFor1StopSplitHerd\n2. Stored Procedure Complexity: Complex\n3. Logic can be replicated in Dataverse using Power Automate: No\n4. Purpose: To extract 1-stop lactation data and populate annual summary tables used for reporting, creating per-lactation and per-herd statistics for the specified year.\n5. Summary of stored procedure:\n- It accepts HerdID, SocietyId and YearNo and computes a date range from Oct 1 of YearNo-1 to Oct 1 of YearNo.\n- It truncates CalcAnnSummSplitHerdAnimalDetails to prepare for fresh calculations.\n- It populates CalcAnnSummSplitHerdAnimalDetails by joining lactation data, totals, and animal details, calculating EndDate305 and various 305-day metrics.\n- It derives CalvingInterval, PedigreeAnimalId, and EndDate for each lactation and sets the Qualifying flag based on date ranges and 305-day criteria.\n- It resolves PedigreeAnimalId by matching to pedigree records, and also attempts mapping via ear tag if required.\n- It updates the evaluation group and removes zero values from key metrics to avoid skewing averages.\n- It loads PIN/PLI data into the calculated records from PTA and associates with the correct pedigree IDs through the evaluation group.\n- It computes herd-level statistics by LactationGroup into CalcAnnSummSplitHerdHerdDetails, including counts of qualifying animals and calculated averages for yields, fats, proteins, cell counts and calving metrics.\n- It adds an All-group total to the herd details to summarise the entire herd across lactation groups.\n- It determines the number of non-qualifying animals per herd and lactation group, stores this in a temporary table, and updates the herd details with NoOfAnimalsNonQualifying.\n- It performs an additional step to calculate the predominant society (via a separate procedure), although the call is commented in the code snippet, indicating orchestration with other routines.\n- The overall flow is designed to extract 1-stop data and populate Storm reporting structures for annual summary purposes."
        },
