         "6": "1. Stored Procedure Name: spu_CreateSacBullResultsOrig\n2. Stored Procedure Complexity: Medium\n3. Logic can be replicated in Dataverse using Power Automate: No\n4. Purpose: To create a duplicate copy of the sac_bull_results_orig table in the SACImport database by copying all rows from sac_bull_results, preserving the IDs so the copy can be compared with the original after amendments.\n5. Summary of stored procedure:\n- The procedure initialises the environment by turning on xact_abort and clears the return code and error text.\n- It checks if the sac_bull_results_orig table already exists in the SACImport database and drops it if found.\n- It creates sac_bull_results_orig by copying all rows from sac_bull_results into SACImport.dbo using a SELECT INTO operation.\n- The full CREATE TABLE statement for sac_bull_results_orig is shown in comments, indicating the intended structure for reference.\n- After creating the copy, it creates a clustered index on evaluation_group_number, PTA_mfp_reliability_lac_all, and herds_with_daughters to optimise queries.\n- It adds a nonclustered primary key on the ID column to enforce row uniqueness and support joins.\n- Additional nonclustered indexes are created on huk_animal_id and on a set of HBN-related columns to improve lookup performance.\n- If all operations succeed, the procedure sets rc to 0 and writes a success message to ErrorText; otherwise, it sets rc to 1 and routes to the error handler."
