         "6": "1. Stored Procedure Name: usp_MobileTCS_ImportIslandData\n2. Stored Procedure Complexity: Complex\n3. Logic can be replicated in Dataverse using Power Automate: No\n4. Purpose: To import Jersey and Guernsey island member data from text files into temporary tables, process and insert into tblMobileFemale and tblMobileMember, update identifiers and attributes, archive source files, and handle errors.\n5. Summary of stored procedure:\n- The procedure imports data from Female.txt and Member.txt into temporary tables tmpMobileFemale and tmpMobileMember.\n- It checks for the existence of the files using xp_cmdshell and returns an error if not found.\n- It retrieves environment directories from zstblTCSSystem for root, import, log, error, and format paths.\n- It seeds the next available AnimalID and CustomerNo from zstblTCSSystemValues and reseeds the temporary tables accordingly.\n- It loads data from the files into the temporary tables using bcp with a specified format file.\n- It updates loaded data for Jersey and Guernsey by setting SocietyID and FieldOfficer, and for Member sets insp_type accordingly.\n- It converts ages to YYMM format and synchronises CustomerNo values between tmpMobileFemale and tmpMobileMember.\n- It converts the numeric prev_class values to alpha codes (P, F, G, GP, VG, EX) where applicable.\n- It assigns a SeqNo to each animal grouped by CustomerNo using a cursor and updates the temporary table.\n- It updates the system values to extend the next AnimalID and CustomerNo counters.\n- It inserts processed data into tblMobileFemale and tblMobileMember with selected fields, mapping various attributes.\n- It renames and archives the processed source files to an Archive folder, moving both Female and Member files.\n- It handles errors by setting an error text and returning a non-zero status if any step fails."
        }
