         "6": "Stored Procedure Name: usp1StopMergeScottishLabResults\nStored Procedure Complexity: Complex\nLogic can be replicated in Dataverse using Power Automate: Yes\nPurpose: To coordinate the merging of Scottish lab results into the system for a specified herd and lab load, validating data integrity, updating tests and milk recordings, handling errors, and marking the result as merged.\nSummary of stored procedure:\n- The procedure usp1StopMergeScottishLabResults takes HerdId, LabLoadId, IgnoreErrors, and an OUTPUT RecordingLoadId, used to locate the latest milk recording for the herd.\n- It declares several local variables and creates a temporary table #ErrMsg to accumulate error messages during validation.\n- It looks up the most recent tblMilkRecordings row for the specified herd and assigns RecordingLoadId, RecordingDate, and LabResultsAdded, ordering by RecordingDate descending.\n- If no recording exists, it logs an error message in #ErrMsg and terminates the procedure.\n- If lab results are already loaded for the latest recording and IgnoreErrors is not 'Y', it logs a warning; otherwise, it exits early when IgnoreErrors='Y'.\n- It checks for duplicate LineNumbers in tblNonRecordedLabResults for the given LabLoadId and aborts with a fatal error if any duplicates are found.\n- It verifies that for each test linked to the RecordingLoadId there is a corresponding lab result; if not, it logs a warning in #ErrMsg.\n- It also checks that there is a LabResult for each test and logs warnings if there is a LabResult for a LineNo without a Test.\n- It computes whether there are any bulk tanks present and counts lab results for LineNumbers 9997, 9998, or 9999; if the numbers don't align, it logs a warning.\n- If no fatal errors exist or IgnoreErrors='Y', it begins a transaction, loads values from tblMilkRecordings to update tests with BFatPercent, ProtPc, CellCount, Urea and Lactose, and copies LabErrorCode; and marks LabResultsAdded = 1 for the recording, and flags the LoadHistory as OneStopScottishLabsMerged = 'Y'.\n- If there are bulk tanks, it updates the corresponding tanks' butterfat, protein, cell counts, Urea and Lactose for the lines representing the tank results (LineNumbers 9997-9999).\n- It also inserts any additional lab results into tblCellCountsOnly for records that have no cow number or missing tests.\n- Finally, it commits the transaction, or shows the accumulated errors in #ErrMsg if errors exist and returns."
        }
